    question: "How is deep cleaning different from regular cleaning?",
    answer: "Regular cleaning focuses on keeping your home fresh and tidy week to week—dusting surfaces, vacuuming/mopping floors, sanitizing kitchens and bathrooms, and maintaining high-traffic areas.\n\nDeep cleaning, on the other hand, goes much further. It targets built-up dirt, grime, and hidden areas that don’t get as much attention during routine cleanings. This includes:\n• Scrubbing baseboards, vents, blinds, and fixtures\n• Cleaning inside cabinets, appliances, and other detailed areas\n• Removing deep buildup in kitchens, bathrooms, and hard-to-reach spaces\n\nIn short, regular cleaning maintains your home, while deep cleaning resets it—leaving every corner spotless and refreshed."
  },
