  },
  {
    question: "How often should I schedule a deep cleaning? And why?",
    answer: "Most homes benefit from a deep cleaning every 3 to 6 months. This frequency helps prevent buildup in kitchens, bathrooms, and hard-to-reach areas while keeping your home healthier and easier to maintain with regular cleanings in between.\n\nYou may want to schedule deep cleaning more often if:\n• You have children, pets, or frequent guests.\n• You host special events and want your home at its best.\n• You notice dust, grime, or buildup in places not covered during routine cleaning.\n\nRegular deep cleaning not only improves your home’s appearance but also extends the life of surfaces, appliances, and finishes—protecting your investment and ensuring a consistently fresh environment."
  }
];



